OL,3,CFamily 'forever heartbroken' as man
OL,4,Cjailed for murder of Rebekah Campbell
OL,6,FThe former boxer and cage fighter
OL,7,Fdenied murdering Rebekah, and instead
OL,8,Fclaimed he was acting in self defence
OL,9,Fwhen he broke into her flat at
OL,10,FKnowsley Heights in Huyton. He was
OL,11,Funanimously convicted of murder by a
OL,12,Fjury in Liverpool.
OL,14,FOrmandy's trial heard he entered her
OL,15,Fflat unannounced wearing a bulletproof
OL,16,Fvest, before Rebekah, 32, collapsed
OL,17,Foutside the block of flats, covered in
OL,18,Fblood, and later died in hospital.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
